# Default egress allowlist. One domain per line; matches the domain and any
# subdomain. `#` comments and blank lines ignored. up.sh unions this with
# EGRESS_ALLOW from .env and writes the result to a `gateway/` dir ALONGSIDE
# $STATE_DIR (deliberately NOT inside it: $STATE_DIR is bind-mounted RW into the
# agent pod, and this file is the gateway's egress policy *over* the agent — under
# $STATE_DIR a compromised agent could whitelist its own exfil host). That dir is
# bind-mounted only into the gateway container. Edit + re-run up.sh → live reload.

# --- GitHub (git over the :8088 cred proxy still resolves these directly) ---
github.com
codeload.github.com
objects.githubusercontent.com
release-assets.githubusercontent.com
raw.githubusercontent.com

# --- Anthropic / Claude Code (authoritative minimal set) ---
# Claude Code authenticates via OAuth (`claude /login`) and reaches Anthropic
# directly through this egress proxy: api.anthropic.com (model API + WebFetch
# preflight), claude.ai + platform.claude.com (OAuth login/refresh).
# Telemetry/sentry/auto-update are OFF via CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_NONESSENTIAL_TRAFFIC
# (deployment.yaml), so statsig/sentry aren't needed. (raw.githubusercontent.com
# is already allowed above — changelog/release feed.)
api.anthropic.com
platform.claude.com
claude.ai
# mcp-proxy.anthropic.com: Claude Code routes ALL claude.ai *bundle* MCP connectors
# (Linear, Slack, Atlassian, …) through https://mcp-proxy.anthropic.com/v1/mcp/<id>
# — the proxy holds the OAuth token and dials the provider server-side. Without
# this, every bundle connector fails (403 Filtered → mcp_unauthorized_no_token).
mcp-proxy.anthropic.com

# --- container registries (image pulls) ---
# Docker Hub serves manifests from registry-1.docker.io but layer blobs redirect
# to a CDN that shifts (CloudFront / Cloudflare / R2). If a pull fails with
# "Filtered" on a *.docker.com or r2 host, add it here.
docker.io
registry-1.docker.io
auth.docker.io
production.cloudfront.docker.com
production.cloudflare.docker.com
ghcr.io
pkg-containers.githubusercontent.com

# --- language / package ecosystems ---
registry.npmjs.org
pypi.org
files.pythonhosted.org
proxy.golang.org
sum.golang.org

# --- OS packages (Debian base images in build pods) ---
deb.debian.org
security.debian.org

# --- code-server extensions (Open VSX, not the MS marketplace) ---
open-vsx.org

# --- DIRECT remote MCP servers (.mcp.json, NOT the claude.ai bundle) ---
# These are only needed for remote MCP servers configured directly in .mcp.json,
# whose token exchange + tool calls DO egress from the pod to the provider. The
# claude.ai *bundle* connectors do NOT need these — they go via mcp-proxy.anthropic.com
# (Anthropic block above). Apex covers mcp.*/auth.*/api.* subdomains.
linear.app
slack.com
atlassian.com

# --- docs / help ---
stackoverflow.com
